<TITLE> ATN Bangla chief sued for slander </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 31 (bdnews24.com)A Supreme Court lawyer on Monday sued private TV channel ATN Bangla chairman Mahfuzur Rahman and five others for defamation. Supreme Court lawyer Saifuddin Mahmud filed the case with Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court, Dhaka. He alleged that a programme, "Bibeker Kachhey Proshno' (question to conscience) aired on Aug 7 had defamatory information about him and termed him 'land grabber'. Magistrate Julfikar Hayat admitted the case after hearing and set Tuesday for the further hearing. The other accused in the case are programme producer and crime affairs correspondent Faisal Mahmud, the director of the programme, Abdul Wadud of Kamarjurim of Joydevpur in Gazipur, Hadis Howlader and Abdul Jabbar Miah of Badekalameshwar. b
